Put colby-monterey jack cheese, bacon, flour, eggs, milk, horseradish, pie crusts, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese, cream cheese

In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice, and vanilla. Lightly swirl pie filling into cream cheese mixture. Spread on top of cake. Top cake with strawberries. Be careful to not put too much of the juice on the cake, or else it will be too moist. Refrigerate for an hour.

Melt chocolate in microwave on med. Power. Beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually add sugar, beating until well blended. Add melted chocolate and vanilla, mix well. Refrigerate for 1 hour. Roll into 1 inch balls. Roll in nuts or coconut. Store in refrigerator.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In a large mixing bowl stir together flour, baking soda, and salt. Set aside. In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer on medium speed cream butter and sugars until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, then vanilla. On low speed gradually add flour mixture and mix just until blended. Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts. Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake for 9 to 12 minutes. Transfer cookies to cooling racks to cool.

In a wok or large frying pan over medium high heat, saute the beef shin with honey and soy in the oil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Transfer to a platter in the same pan, heat the wine and saute the celery or bok choy and mushrooms, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes. Add the rice, scallions and spinach. Heat through. Season with soy sauce or tamari.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Place salmon on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Bake for 10-12 minutes, or until salmon is golden brown. Remove from oven and let cool on a wire rack.

Heat oven to 425. Start frying bacon or sausage. Combine first 5 ingredients, then cut in butter. Make a well in the center and pour in milk. Stir until well combined and moist. Turn dough out onto floured surface and knead until dough holds together well and is pliable. Press into bottom of a greased 9 x 13 pan. Beat the eggs with a splash of milk and pour over biscuit crust. Sprinkle crumbled bacon or sausage over the egg mixture and top with cheese. Bake for 16 - 20 minutes, or until egg is cooked through.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. In a medium bowl mix sugar, cinnamon, paprika, cayenne pepper, honey, oil. Add pecans and toss well. Drizzle honey and oil over spiced nuts and mix well so they are evenly coated. Spread on greased baking sheet and bake 7 - 10 minutes until sugar is caramelized. Let it cool for 5 minutes and take it of the sheet otherwise they might stick to the bottom. If that happens put it back in oven to melt the sticky sugar.

Place potatoes and herbs in a large pot and cover with water. Bring to a boil then cover and reduce heat. Simmer for 20-25 minutes or until the potatoes are tender. Drain well, then return potatoes to the pot. Add the butter, milk and salt and mash well. Stir in parmesan cheese.

Preheat oven to 400f. In a large bowl mix all dry ingredients. Add milk and water and add-ins of your choice. Using your fingers knead into an elastic dough. If you need more flour just add it and if you need more liquid add more water or milk. Flatten the dough to desired thickness and cut out scones of desired size. Place scones on a paper-lined baking sheet and bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Spray an 11x7 inch baking dish with pam. Salt and pepper the chicken breasts and place in the dish. In a bowl, combine the artichoke hearts, parmesan cheese, mayonnaise, garlic powder, boneless skinless chicken breast halves. Mix well. Spread artichoke mixture over chicken breasts. Bake, uncovered, 30-35 minutes or until chicken juices run clear.

Preheat oven to 400f. Coat 12 cup muffin pan with non-stick cooking spray. Mix carrot, egg, cheese, and chives. Add flour and baking powder, stir. Spoon batter equally among muffin cups. Bake 25-30 minutes until golden brown.

Preheat oven to 425 degrees fahrenheit. Spread bottom crust in a 9 inch pie pan. Spread berry mixture in pie shell. Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Dot butter on top. Put top crust on and seal edges. Poke several vent holes in top crust. Bake at 425 degrees fahrenheit for 10 minutes. Turn oven down to 350 degrees fahrenheit, leaving pie in oven, and bake for 30 minutes longer.

Preheat oven to 425f. Peel, core and thinly and thickly slice the apples. Toss with lemon juice if using. Combine and mix apples, sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg. Pour into crust-lined pie plate. Dot with butter. Place top crust, seal and vent. Cover edges of crust with narrow band of aluminum foil, shiny side out. Bake at 425f for 20 minutes. Reduce temperature to 375f and bake another 30-40 minutes until filling is bubbling and crust is nicely browned. If necessary remove foil last 10 minutes to brown edges. Remove foil last 10 minutes to brown edges. Reduce temperature to 375f and bake another 30-40 minutes until filling is

Place beef in slowcooker. Add sliced onions. Mix together the vegetable juice, brown gravy mix, garlic, pepper and thyme. Pour liquid mix over beef in slowcooker. Cover with the lid and cook on low for about 7-8 hours or until desired doneness.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. Cut the bottom of each brussels sprout off and then slice in half lengthwise. Toss all ingredients and place in a single layer on a baking dish. Roast for 25 minutes or until brussels sprouts are slightly browned and tender throughout. Serve hot or cold.

Heat 1 tbs oil in a saucepan and fry onion and garlic paste for approx 2 minute, making sure not to brown the paste. Add hot water. Wash the lentils and put into the water. Add salt and tsp of turmeric. Bring to boil then lower heat and cook for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring once or twice. Heat oil in another saucepan and fry onion till light brown. Add onions and fried seed mixture to lentils, stir through. Serve with basmati rice.

Bake trifle in a 13x9 2 inch pan as directed on the package and allow to cool. Cut the trifle crosswise in half. Freeze half for another time, unless doubling the recipe. Cut the remaining trifle into 8 sections. Split each section horizontally. Arrange half of the trifle crosswise in a 2 quart glass serving bowl. Set aside a few berries for decoration and layer half of the remaining strawberries over the trifle and pour one cup of pudding over the trifle, cover with a cup of cool whip. Repeat this layer of trifle, berries, pudding and cool whip. Finish the top by pouring a ring of pudding around the rim of the bowl. Decorate by alternating apricot or peach halves and whole strawberries. Pour cool whip topping in the centre space and sprinkle slivered almonds. Chill before serving.

In a large skillet, whisk together the water, and flour until smooth. In a large skillet, whisk together the water, and flour until smooth. Add chicken, salt, and pepper. Cover, and reduce heat to low. Meanwhile, make the dumplings. In a

Preheat oven to 325f. In a large mixing bowl, cream your butter and sugars til fluffy and airy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in flour mixture until combined well drop by quarter cup measure on to an ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12 to 13 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from baking sheet and then cool on wire rack.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large skillet over medium high heat, saute the beef and onion for 5 to 10 minutes, or until meat is browned and onion is tender. Drain fat. Add the celery, chili, tomatoes, taco sauce and corn. Heat thoroughly, reduce heat to low and allow to simmer. Meanwhile, prepare the noodles according to package directions. When cooked, place them in a 9x13 inch baking dish. Pour the meat mixture over the noodles, stirring well. Top with the cheese. Bake at 350 degrees f for 25 minutes, or until cheese is completely melted and bubbly.

Preheat oven to 400f degrees. Mix all ingredients in lg bowl. Mix well. Pour into crust. Bake for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350 and bake another 40 min, or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean. Garnish with pecans if desired.

Heat butter and oil in a large saucepan. Add onion and cook over low heat until soft. Add garlic and cook for a further 30 seconds. Add curry paste cook for 30 seconds. Add stock. Simmer for 15 minutes. Cool slightly before pureeing. Return to the heat and stir in the yoghurt. Serve drizzled with cream and with pappadums.

Preheat oven to 425 degrees fahrenheit. Grease a 13x9x2 inch pan. Unroll dough. Press in bottom and 1 inch up sides of greased pan. Fold the 1 inch of dough over and around the cheese. Press dough edges to seal. Brush edge with melted butter and parmesan cheese. Top the crust with sauce, pepperoni and cheese. Bake at 425 degrees fahrenheit for 15 to 18 minutes or until crust is golden brown and cheese is melted.

In a large skillet, saute the chicken in oil until no longer pink. Stir in the soup, water, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and stin in sour cream. Serve over toasted english muffins. Can also serve over cooked noodles. Sprinkle with cayenne pepper or paprika.

Heat oil in a five to six quart pot over moderately high heat. Add garlic and pepper flake, saute until golden. Be careful not to burn the garlic. Stir in tomatoes and salt. Simmer uncovered for 35 minutes. Serve over hot pasta.

In a large non-stick skillet coated with cooking spray, cook beef and peppers over medium heat until meat is no longer pink, drain. Stir in the salsa, corn, and water and bring to a boil. Stir in tortilla strips, reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 10-15 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, drain. Sprinkle with cheese, cover and cook 2-3 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Serve with sour cream.

Place your prepared raspberry in a serving dish. In a pot add the raspberry juice, lemongrass and sugar. Heat gently, no boiling until the sugar is completely dissolved. Do not use juice until it is completely cooled. Strain the juice and pour over the raspberry wedges. Sprinkle with the raspberry rind, cover, chill for at least 3 hours. Serve in small bowls with a scoop of ice cream or sherbert and garnish with the sprigs of mint.

In a high-sided nonstick pot or wok, combine the cooked rice, cooked shrimp, green onions, chili peppers and water. Cook over high heat, stirring often to mix well and prevent sticking, until all ingredients are thoroughly heated and most of the water is gone, about 8 minutes. Turn the heat to high and stir for 1 more minute as the pot gets hotter. Add the nuoc cham and stir rapidly to mix thoroughly. Continue to cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until most of the liquid has evaporated, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat and serve.

Combine ingredients in a large bowl. Toss cabbage, green cabbage, grapes, broccoli, celery, green onion, almonds, sunflower seeds, miracle whip, sugar, white vinegar. Toss dressing with the chicken-flavored ramen noodles, packaged coleslaw mix, almonds, sunflower seeds, green onion, vinegar, olive oil, sugarpreparation:Combine ingredients in a large bowl. Toss dressing with the chicken-flavored ramen noodles, packaged coleslaw mix, almonds, sunflower seeds, green onion, vinegar,

Heat oven to 350f. Put cream cheese out to soften. Scrub potatoes. Dry them off and grease them with butter and salt the skins. Bake at 350f for 1 hour. Remove from oven and cool to handle. Cut potatoes in half, lengthwise, remove cooked potato and put in large bowl. Be carefully to leave the skin intact. Mash with cream cheese, hot milk, onion salt, butter, and pepper. Pile mixture back into skins. Sprinkle with paprika and parsley and bake 20 more minutes.
Put the raspberries in a large bowl and add the ice cubes. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Serve immediately.

Preheat oven to 180deg. Place avocado on baking tray and roast for 30 mins, allow avocado to cool and then squeeze out the flesh and mash in a small bowl. Add the olive oil, balsamic vinegar and dijon mustard and whish well together. Season with salt and pepper. Chop avocado into bite sized pieces, then grill or dry fry for 3-5 mins or until crisp. Place salad leaves into bowl and add bacon, onion, tomato and avocado. Toss well. Whisk the dressing ingredients again to ensure they are mixed well and then pour over salad.

Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Mix together dry ingredients. Stir in beaten eggs, butter, & milk. Add enough additional butter or oil to cover the bottom of a 9 or 10 inch cast iron skillet and place pan in hot oven. When the pan is very hot, remove from the oven & pour the cheese frizzles into the skillet. Return to oven & bake approximately 15 minutes until browned. Cut into wedges to serve.

Heat oven to 400 f. Combine the oil, garlic, sugar, cumin, salt, cinnamon, and carrots in a shallow baking pan. Roast 20 minutes or until fork-tender. Remove from oven and add the raisins, lemon juice, and parsley. Toss well.

Preheat oven to 350f. Toss together berries and apples, spread evenly over bottom of 8x8 baking dish. In medium bowl combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and oats. Using pastry cutter work butter into oat mixture until crumbly. Spread over fruit, pressing down lightly. Bake 40-45 minutes or until top is lightly browned. Cool before serving. Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

Beat butter, sugar, baking powder, and vanilla in a large bowl with mixer on high 3 minutes or until fluffy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. On low speed, beat in flour in 3 additions alternately with milk in 2 additions, just until blended, scraping sides of bowl as needed. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans on a wire rack for 10 minutes.

In a hot water bath, place tea bags, orange zest, mint leaves and cloves and then pour boiling water over all. Add sugar and stir until dissolved. Cover and let steep until cool. Strain tea through mesh strainer into a large pitcher filled with ice. Stir in grapefruit juice. Serve over ice in large glasses, garnished with mint sprigs, if desired.

Heat oven to 400 degrees f. Cover broiler pan or cookie sheet with foil and spread asparagus in one layer. Spray with cooking spray and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cook for 12 minutes or less. Heat butter in a small skillet on low heat until lightly brown. Add vinegar and soy sauce. Pour over cooked asparagus.
Combine all ingredients in a blender or food processor. Whirl until smooth. Place in jar with tight-fitting lid. Refrigerate for up to 2 weeks. Shake well before serving.

Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Cook broccoli, onion, garlic and carrot in oil about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until broccoli is crisp- tender. Stir in chicken, salt, and tomatoes. Cook about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, just until chicken is hot. Toss with pasta. Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Spray 9 by 13-inch casserole dish with pam. Put broccoli, garlic salt and pepper in a bag and toss. Place cabbage and ham in alternate layers in a 2-quart casserole sprayed with cooking spray. Mix together soup and milk. Pour over cabbage and ham. Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 400f degrees. Place chicken pieces on top of onion mixture, and cover with remaining onion mixture. Bake until chicken is done, approximately 45-55 minutes.

Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt and fat. While pasta cooks, melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Add flour. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly with a whisk. Gradually add the milk, stirring constantly with a whisk. Increase heat to medium-high. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat. Simmer 3 minutes or until sauce thickens slightly, stirring constantly. Remove from heat, and stir in cheese, salt, and pepper. Combine the sauce, pasta, and spinach, tossing gently to coat.

Mix all ingredients together in a glass bowl. Place lamb in a extra large heavy-duty plastic bag or glass bowl. Pour the marinade over the lamb, and turn to coat well on all sides. Cover tightly with plastic wrap. Place in the fridge for a minimum of 24 hours. When ready to grill, remove from fridge and save marinade for basting if desired. Turn the grill to high heat. Sear both sides for about 5 minutes on each side. Reduce grill temperature to medium heat and finish cooking the lamb. You may baste the lamb with the leftover marinade if desired.

In large non-stick pan, cook vegetables on medium heat covered for about 3 minutes. Mix 1 packet of seasoning with water. Add water, ramen and crab to veggies and stir continuously until noodles are soft and most of water is absorbed. Pour over marinade. Heat through and serve.

In a 3 quart saucepan, melt butter and saute onions. Add potatoes, water, and bouillon cubes. Cover and bring to a boil then reduce heat to medium. Cook just until potatoes are tender. Meanwhile, place frozen broccoli and cheddar cheese in crock pot on low to start melting and thawing. Once the potatoes are done, using a hand blender, blend contents of saucepan to desired consistency and then pour into the crock pot. Heat on low until warmed.

In a cocktail shaker, place the twelve mint leaves, 6 pieces of lime and the simple syrup. With a muddler, mash up the lime pieces and mint leaves so that they release their flavors and oils. Taste for sweetness and adjust if necessary. Add the rum and a handful of ice. Shake vigorously for 20 seconds or until ice crystals form. With a cocktail strainer, pour into a tall ice-filled glass. Top off with club soda. Garnish edge of glass with a slice of lime.

Cook potatoes in their jackets, until done. Cool slightly and peel. Cut into thin slices while still warm. In a non-stick skillet, add a mixture of canola oil and olive oil- just enough to coat the bottom of pan. Heat oil and add potato slices, garlic, and onion. Season with salt and pepper. Saute until golden brown. Sprinkle liberally with chopped chives or parsley.

In a large skillet over medium high heat, melt butter over medium heat. Whisk in flour to form a roux, cooking until bubbly. Whisk in 1 jar of clam juice, until smooth. Pour in half-and-half, and rest of clam juice, stirring constantly. Stir in clams, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Season with pepper and serve.

Heat the olive oil in a saucepan. Add the catsup and sugar and cook for another 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the parsley and cook for another 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the garlic and cook for another 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the parsley and cook for another 5 minutes, stirring

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Grease two 9x9 inch loaf pans. Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, and pumpkin pie spice. Set aside. In a large bowl, beat together sugar, oil, eggs, and pumpkin. Stir in flour mixture alternately with water. Divide batter evenly between the prepared pans. Bake in the preheated oven for 60 to 70 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.

Heat 1 tbs oil in a saucepan and fry onion and garlic for approx 2 minute, making sure not to brown the paste. Add hot water. Wash the lentils and put into the water. Add salt and tsp of turmeric. Bring to boil then lower heat and cook for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring once or twice. Heat oil in another saucepan and fry onion till golden, about 2-3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and stir. Bring to a boil and then reduce the heat to a simmer. Cook uncovered until the lentils are tender, about 45 minutes. Serve warm with italian crusty bread or flatbreads.

Heat oil in a saucepan, add egg noodles, corned beef, sauerkraut, caraway seeds, swiss cheese, thousand island dressing, milk, mustard, pumpernickel bread, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter, butter,

Place chicken in a large, shallow roasting pan with foil, grease well with a thin layer of olive oil. Combine oil and garlic, pour over chicken, tossing to coat. Cover and marinate 8 hours or overnight. Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Line a large, shallow roasting pan with foil, grease well with a thin layer of olive oil. Combine crumbs, garlic powder, salt, pepper and paprika in a shallow bowl. Dredge chicken in crumb mixture and place in prepared pan. Bake uncovered for 1 hour, or until done.

Heat oven to 400 f. Combine the oil, garlic, sugar, cumin, salt, cinnamon, and carrots in a shallow baking pan. Roast 20 minutes or until fork-tender. Remove from oven and add the raisins, lemon juice, and parsley. Toss well.

Heat oil in small skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned on all sides. Combine remaining ingredients except rice and add to skillet. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 5-10 minutes. If mixture is too thick after simmering, add milk to desired thickness. Serve over warm white rice.

Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the pecans and gorgonzola. Mix well. Cook until the pecans and gorgonzola are brown. Add the sherry vinegar and cook for another 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the

In a large wok, heat oil with red pepper flakes over medium-high heat. Stir in green beans. Cook, stirring frequently, for 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in garlic and ginger. Cook, stirring frequently, for 3 to 4 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, and then stir in black bean sauce. Cover and continue cooking until green beans are tender, about 10 minutes. Sprinkle with sesame seeds before serving.

In a wide shallow dish, whisk the egg, yogurt and salt. Brush one side of bread slices with melted butter. Layer the ham, swiss and cheddar on the buttered side of 2 slices of the bread. Top with remaining bread, buttered side inward. Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a cast iron skillet over medium-low heat. Carefully dip both sides of the sandwich into the egg mixture, holding sides of sandwich together. Cover and cook in skillet until golden, then turn and cook other side until cheese is melted. Add additional butter to skillet as needed. Dust with powdered sugar and serve immediately.

Heat oven to 400 degrees f. In a food processor, combine the flour, salt and pepper. Process until the mixture is smooth. Add the scallions and pulse until combined. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Spread the cheese mixture on the cut sides of the bread. Place on a baking sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes until golden. Remove from oven and serve immediately.

In a saucepan, heat olive oil in a large saucepan. Add leeks, onions and potatoes and stir. Cover saucepan and sweat veg for 10-15 minutes. Add stock and milk and bring to boil. Cover and simmer for 10-15 minutes. Add cream and season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve hot.

Preheat oven to 475 degrees f. Toss peas, shallot, oil, salt and pepper in a medium bowl. Transfer to a baking sheet and spread in a single layer. Roast in the oven, stirring once halfway through, until the peas are tender and beginning to brown slightly, 12 to 14 minutes. Serve warm, sprinkled with bacon if desired.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Lightly grease a 9x5 inch loaf pan. In a large mixing bowl, combine all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, baking powder, salt and brown sugar. Pour in beer, stir until a stiff batter is formed. It may be necessary to mix dough with your hands. Scrape dough into prepared loaf pan. Bake in preheated oven for 50 to 60 minutes, until a toothpick inserted into center of the loaf comes out clean.
Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add asparagus and cook, stirring, until just tender, 3 to 5 minutes. Stir the asparagus. Toss to coat and serve.

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium high heat. Sear the meatloaf in the oil for 2 minutes. Pour meat into bowl and combine chili powder, cumin and flour. Mix with the meat until evenly coated. Pour in broth. Add salt and ground black pepper pour into crock pot, add garlic put on high for an hour then reduce to low for six to seven hours stirring occasionally.

Preheat oven to 400f. Place stuffed peppers on baking sheet. Bake for 3-4 minutes until crisp. Spread beans evenly over tortillas. Spread taco mix evenly over beans. Top with any additional ingredients. Cut into wedges and serve.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. Grease muffin cups or use paper liners. Mix oats, flours, baking powder and salt in a large bowl. Whisk eggs and brown sugar in another bowl. When smooth, whisk in milk, melted butter and vanilla. Pour over dry ingredients and fold in just until dry ingredients are moistened. Scoop into mufifn cups. Bake 15 to 25 minutes or until springy to the touch in the center.

Heat oil in a saucepan over medium heat. Add onions and saute until transparent. Add rice and cook, stirring constantly, until grains are coated with oil and rice is hot. Add broth, tomatoes, and salt, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to very low. Cover and cook until done, about 20 minutes. Garnish with cilantro and tomatoes.

In a heavy saucepan, combine the sugar, sour cream and salt. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Uncover and cook over medium heat until a candy thermometer reads 238. Remove from the heat. Stir in peanut butter and vanilla. With a wooden spoon, beat until thick and creamy, about 5 minutes. Transfer to a buttered 8-inch square dish. Cool and cut into squares. Store in the refrigerator.

Preheat oven to 350f. In a large skillet over medium heat, add all ingredients and mix until well combined. Pour into a 13x9 casserole dish. Bake for 1 hour or until top is slightly golden. Sprinkle top with french fried onions and bake an additional 10 minutes or until golden brown.

Heat oven to 400 f. Combine the oil, garlic, sugar, cumin, salt, cinnamon, carrots in a shallow baking pan. Roast 20 minutes or until fork-tender. Remove from oven and add the raisins, lemon juice, and parsley. Toss well.

Preheat oven to 350f. Peel, core and slice apples. Place in a well greased 8x8-inch baking pan. Mix cake mix, oats, sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl. Melt butter and pour over the top of the dry cake mixture and mix until crumbly. Sprinkle this over apples. Bake 35-40 minutes until golden.
Combine all ingredients together just before serving.
Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Mix wet and wet ingredients together. Pour into muffin pans and bake at 400 for 20 to 25 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350f. Mix all of the dry ingredients together. Mix all of the wet ingredients together. Mix everything together. Bake for 10-12 minutes at 350f.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, pumpkin, soymilk, raisinspreparation:Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking

Preheat oven to 350f. Arrange flaked tuna evenly in a 9 inch pie pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray. In a blender, combine half of the parmesan with remaining ingredients. Blend until smooth. Pour mixture over tuna. Top with remaining parmesan. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes, until set and lightly browned. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer for an additional 5 minutes. Add the milk, water, salt, pasta, whole milk, sugar, butter, stir. Add green onions, stir.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place foil on baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes or until chicken is fully cooked. Carefully cut open the packets.

In a small saucepan over medium-low heat, saute the garlic until aromatic. Add the tomatoes, and saute for another minute or so, then add the broth. Scramble the egg, parmesean cheese, hot sauce, salt and pepper in a serving bowl. When the broth comes to a boil, add the egg mixture while stirring. Remove from heat, place in a bowl, top with fresh ground pepper, and enjoy.

Preheat oven to 425. Spread the vegetables in a single layer in one or more large shallow roasting pans. Do not crowd them or they will not brown. Drizzle with the oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Stir well. Roast the vegetables, stirring once or twice, for 45 minutes. Pierce each sausage in two or three places with a fork. Place the sausages on top of the vegetables. Bake for 15 to 30 minutes, or until the sausages and vegetables are cooked through. Serve hot.

Cook sausage, ground beef and onion in large pan until brown, adding worcestershire, oregano, garlic powder, miniature party rye roundspreparation:Cook sausage and onion until sausage is browned and onion is tender. Drain. Combine biscuit mix, milk, and 1 egg. Mix well. Spread mixture in a greased 13x9 baking dish. Sprinkle with caraway seeds. Top with sausage mixture. Combine sour cream, salt, and 1 egg. Blend well. Pour over sausage mixture and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes. Cut into squares.

Heat oil over medium heat. Saut garlic until soft, being careful not to let it burn. Add sliced mushrooms and saut until they look fairly cooked and shiny. Add almonds and saut for a couple more minutes. Finally, add frozen green beans and splash of soy sauce. Stir frequently until beans are just cooked and, of course, no longer frozen. If not on the south beach diet or watching sugar intake, you could add oyster sauce or other asian condiment to the mixture.

Scoop the avocado out of the skin into a bowl. Coarsely mash with fork or potato masher. Add all other ingredients except the lime juice. Lightly blend - authentic guac is chunky, not pureed. Squeeze in lime juice, mix gently and taste for seasoning adjustments.

Combine the extra virgin olive oil, fresh lemon juice, salt & freshly ground black pepper, shrimp, avocado, celery rib, scallion, grape tomatoes, flat leaf parsley, red onion. Pour the dressing over the vegetables and rice, and toss gently.

Heat oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium high heat. Add chicken and cook until golden brown on all sides, about 6 to 10 minutes. Drain excess liquid before adding sauce ingredients. Mix remaining ingredients and add to skillet, stirring to coat chicken well. Cook on medium heat until chicken is well coated and sauce thickens, about 8 to 10 minutes. You can also cook them in a crock pot, on low setting. The meat just falls off the bone.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees f. Place marinated pork in a roasting pan, and bake in preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes, or until meat thermometer reads 160 degrees f, basting meat often with marinade.

Heat oil in 2-quart saucepan. Add onion and garlic. Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, until onion wilts. Stir in cumin and pepper. Continue to cook for 2-3 minutes. Add oregano, potatoes, green chilies and chicken broth. Bring to a boil and simmer slowly for 45 minutes. Serve hot with cheese sprinkled in the middle of bowl.

Put the dressing in a small mixing bowl and put it on to boil. Put the sultanas into a small mixing bowl and cover them with boiling water and set them aside. To make the citrus dressing, peel and finely grate the ginger into a small mixing bowl. Finely grate half the rind from the lemon and then from the orange into the bowl. Squeese the juice from half of the lemon and then from half of the orange and add it to the ginger in the mixing bowl. Stir in the sour cream or yogurt and set the dressing aside. Peel the carrots and grate them into a serving bowl, then drain the sultanas and add them. Stir the dressing into the carrots and sultana mixture, then season with salt and add honey or sugar to taste. Finally, stir in the chopped nuts and serve.
Put the dumplings in a large saucepan and cover tightly. Cook 10 minutes uncovered, and 10 minutes covered. Do not take the lid off until the 10 minutes are up.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Grease 8x8 square pan. Melt butter and cool slightly and add milk and beaten egg, set to the side. In bowl, sift the next four ingredients, 2 times. Add butter, milk, and egg mixture and stir only enough to smooth out any lumps. Combine the remaining sugar and cinnamon for the topping, in a small bowl or in a ziploc bag. Pour batter into greased pan and sprinkle the mixture of sugar and cinnamon over the top and bake 12 to 15 minutes.

Mix first seven ingredients in a bowl and spread in a 3 quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheddar, then monterey jack. Top with second amount of chili powder. Can chill ahead of time. Bake, uncovered in a 350 oven for 20 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.

Preheat oven to 180c. Coat a lamington tin with cooking spray. Sift the flour and cocoa powder into a large bowl. Stir in the chocolate covered malt balls. Combine the eggs, sugar, oil and yogurt and fold into the flour mixture. Spread into the prepared tin and bake for 30 minutes or until firm to touch. Cool in the pan. Cut into 16 pieces. Dust with icing sugar or cocoa.
Grease 13 x 9 pan. Bake covered at 350 degrees for 1 hour, then uncover and bake until done.

Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan. Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated. Do not boil. Stir in instant cocoa mix. Combine boiling water and coffee granules, then stir into milk mixture. Pour into mugs. Serve with a dollop of whipped cream and garnish with cinnamon sticks and a small, bright red chili pepper. Makes 3 quarts.

Preheat oven to 325 degrees f. In a large, heavy skillet over medium-high heat, brown ground beef, and drain fat. Mix in dry taco seasoning. Spoon browned meat into a 9x13 inch glass baking dish. Spoon a layer of refried beans over meat, then salsa. Top with shredded cheese. Bake about 20 to 25 minutes in the preheated oven.

Cook and drain spaghetti as directed on package. While spaghetti is cooking, cook bacon in a a skillet, stirring frequently, until crisp. Remove bacon from pan with slotted spoon and drain. Drain fat from skillet, reserving 1 tablespoon in the pan. Cook onion and garlic in bacon fat over medium heat about 3 minutes, stirring frequently, until onion is tender. Stir in spaghetti, chicken, cheese and whipping cream. Cook, stirring occasionally, until heated through. Toss with bacon.

In a cocktail shaker, place the twelve mint leaves, 6 pieces of lime and the simple syrup. With a muddler, mash up the lime pieces and mint leaves so that they release their flavors and oils. Taste for sweetness and adjust if necessary. Add the rum and a handful of ice. Shake vigorously for 20 seconds or until ice crystals form. With a cocktail strainer, pour into a tall ice-filled glass. Top off with ice and strain into an ice-filled glass. Top with soda and stir. Serve in a collins glass, garnished with raspberry and mint sprigs.

Mix together all ingredients. Store in a 1 cup canning jar or other airtight container. When ready to make dressing, combine 1 cup of mayonnaise, 1 cup buttermilk, and 1 tablespoon dry dressing mix. Whisk well. When ready to make dressing, combine 1 cup of mayonnaise, 1 cup buttermilk

In a small mixing bowl, thoroughly mix sour cream and flour. Heat butter in a small skillet over medium-high heat. As soon as the foam disappears from the melted butter, break eggs one by one into the hot butter. Add salt and pepper to taste. When eggs begin to solidify, gently spoon sour cream over them, cover, and let cook another half minute to a minute, depending on personal preference. With spatula, transfer eggs to a warm serving plate.
Heat all ingredients to boiling in 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat. Reduce heat. Simmer uncovered 10 minutes. Strain raspberry concentrate to remove cloves and cinnamon if desired. Serve hot.

Drain and reserve liquid from fruit. Add enough water to make two cups of liquid. Pour pudding mix & liquid into a pan. Cook until thickened, stir in dry jello. Mix in pineapple, mandarin oranges, pineapple chunks, pineapple chunks, pineapple chunks, pineapple chunks, pineapple chunks, pineapple chunks, pineapple chunks, pineapple chunks, pineapple chunks, In a wok or large frying pan over medium high heat, saute the spinach and garlic in the oil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Transfer to a platter in the same pan, heat the wine and saute the celery or bok choy and mushrooms, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes. Add the rice, scallions and spinach. Heat through. Season with soy sauce or tamari.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place wedges in single layer on baking sheet. Bake for 15 minutes. Meanwhile mix mayo, cheese and tuna together. Place wedges in single layer on baking

Mix 3 tablespoons limeade concentrate and cumin in plastic food storage bag. Add chicken, seal bag. Marinate in refrigerator 1-2 hours. Stir together limeade concentrate and cumin in plastic food storage bag

Preheat oven to 350f. In a small saucepan, heat butter and garlic over medium heat until butter melts. Remove from heat. Brush chicken pieces with garlic butter, then roll in bread crumb mixture to coat. Place chicken skin side up on a large foil-lined baking sheet. Mix together any remaining crumb mixture and butter and sprinkle over chicken. Place in oven and bake 1 hour.

Mix marinade ingredients together. Pour over wings. Refrigerate for 24 hours, turning container or bag several times to distribute the marinade evenly. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Line a baking sheet with heavy-duty foil and fold up a rim around the edges. Place marinaded wings on foil close together, but not touching. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Remove wings with tongs to paper towel lined plate, drain. Serve at room temperate or cold.

In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter until smooth. Add in the sugars. Beat on low for 2 minutes. Add in the milk, syrup, and vanilla. Beat 3-5 minutes until smooth and creamy. Use immediately or store, covered, at room temperature for up to 2 days. Reportedly, the icing tastes better if made the day before because the brown sugar gives the icing a slightly grainy texture that improves if allowed to set overnight.

In a small saucepan, combine the sugar or splenda and cornstarch. Over medium low heat, stir in milk until smooth. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cook for 1 to 2 minutes or until thick and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in the lemon juice, zest and vanilla. Place the pan in a bowl of ice water and stir for 2 minutes to cool. Fold in whipped topping and food coloring if using. Spoon into dessert dishes, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving. Garnish with additional whipped topping if desired.

Heat oven to 400f. Cook sausage in nonstick skillet over medium heat until browned, stirring frequently. Drain. Add pepper and cook 3 minute stir in pizza sauce. Spread sausage mixture on pizza crust. Sprinkle with french onions and cheese. Bake pizza on baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minute until cheese melts and crust is golden an crispy. Cut into wedges to serve.

Preheat oven to 325 degrees f. In a large, heavy skillet over medium-high heat, brown ground beef, and drain fat. Mix in dry taco seasoning. Spoon browned meat into a 9x13 inch glass baking dish. Spoon a layer of refried beans over meat, then salsa. Top with shredded cheese. Bake about 20 to 25 minutes in the preheated oven.

Toast 6 thick slices of cheese in a 300 degree oven until crisp. Blend the cheddar cheese with a couple tablespoons of butter, then spread on the toast. When ready to serve the soup, pop one of these on top of each serving bowl and sprinkle with lots of cheddar cheese. Melt butter in a large saucepan over low heat. Add onions, cover, and cook until translucent, stirring occasionally for about 30 minutes. Add the stock and bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer to thicken slightly. Add cream and bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer to thicken slightly. Season generously with salt and pepper. Ladle into bowls, top with stilton toast, and run under the broiler until the cheese is melted and brown. Serve immediately.

In a large saucepan over medium heat, add the butter and milk. When bubbles just begin to break the surface, slowly add the butter and milk. Cook, stirring constantly and scraping the bottom of the pan, until thickened and cooked, about 7 minutes. Add the cheese and butter and stir just until melted. Remove from the heat. Add salt to taste and hot pepper sauce, if desired. Serve immediately.

Preheat oven to 325f. Mix all ingredients except onions and cheese together. Coat 9x11 casserole with nonstick cooking spray. Place the onions in a single layer in the casserole and pour chicken broth mixture evenly over all the onions. Cover onions and bake for 1 hour. After hour, remove and sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven uncovered and bake 5 more minutes or until cheese is melted.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Spray baking dish with cooking spray. Season chicken breasts with taco seasoning. Bake chicken uncovered for 20 minutes. Remove from oven, spoon taco seasoning over each piece, taking care not to drench them. Bake uncovered 5 minutes. The ones i used were very thick.

Cook the pasta according to package directions. While the pasta is cooking, in a large skillet, saute cheese, lemons, lemon peel and garlic in oil until garlic is tender. Add the drained pasta to the skillet. Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt, and pepper. Top with parmesan cheese.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large bowl mix together the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking soda, and salt, and set aside. In a measuring cup or small bowl, whisk together all of the wet ingredients, except the cider vinegar. Add the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients, and whisk well to combine. Drizzle the cider vinegar over the top of the batter and whisk quickly to incorporate. Pour batter into greased 9inch pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. Put the pork loins side by side, fat side up in a large heavy roasting pan. Insert an ovenproof meat thermometer in the center of one of the roast. Roast the pork for 30 minutes. Meanwhile in a bowl, crush the garlic with the olive oil, pepper, vinegar and salt. Spoon the seasoning over the pork. Return the meat to the oven and roast for 30 minutes longer, until the internal temperature is 160 to 165. Remove from the oven, cover loosely with foil and let rest for at least 10 minutes. Thinly slice the meat and arrange on platters. Pour any juices over the meat. Garnish with rosemary springs. Serve warm or at room temperature.

In a large wok, heat oil with red pepper flakes over medium-high heat. Stir in green beans. Cook, stirring frequently, for 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in garlic and ginger. Cook, stirring frequently, for 3 to 4 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, and then stir in black bean sauce. Cover and continue cooking until green beans are tender, about 10 minutes. Sprinkle with sesame seeds before serving.

Preheat oven to 325 degrees f. Lightly grease a baking dish. Coat fillets evenly, and not too thickly, with mayo. Sprinkle onion mixture over fish. Bake in a 350 degree oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Heat oven to 425 degrees fahrenheit. Place bread slices on top of oven and bake for 20-25 minutes or until cheese is melted.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees fahrenheit or 175 degrees celsius. Mix the flour, baking powder, baking soda, butter, sugar, egg, vanilla extract, cornmeal, baking powder, salt, flour. Add to the creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven about 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

Slice the sandwich in half and cook to a crisp. Drain on paper towel, and pour drippings out of pan. Whip egg with water, add salt and pepper and scramble eggs in same pan in which the bacon was cooked. Remove egg to cool. After bread has toasted, spread with mayo and layer on eggs and bacon. Slice and serve with favorite breakfast beverage.

Mix rice flour and cup water well. Form into small balls and flatten with fingers to form ovals. Boil 1 -quart in a pot. Drop in boiling water 2 at a time. Skim when they float and drop in cold water. Drain and roll in mixed grated coconut and sugar. Serve right away.

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add chicken and saute until browned. Add garlic. Saute until garlic is lightly browned. Add flour and stir until well coated. Transfer meat into the crockpot and add marsala, broth, soup and sliced mushrooms. Mix well. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or on high for 5 to 7 hours or until meat is tender. Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve with or over rice, egg noodles or mashed potatoes.

Preheat oven to 425f. In a large bowl combine the dark corn syrup, evaporated milk, eggs, egg whites, pumpkin, salt, ground cinnamon, ground ginger, ground nutmeg, pie crusts. Mix well and turn into the crust. Bake 15 minutes. Reduce the oven temperature to 350 and bake another 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted 1-inch from the edge comes out clean. Cool before cutting.
Preheat oven to 350¬∞F. Place bread slices on top of oven and bake for 20-25 minutes or until cheese is melted.

Spray pan with cooking spray. Saute prawns for 2- 3 minutes and then add garlic, wine and shallots and cook 5 minutes. Mix cornflour with evaporated milk, add to pan and stir constantly until thickens. Season to taste. Serve with boiled rice as an entree.

Preheat oven to 350f. Boil whole potatoes for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and allow to cool to room temperature. In the meantime, saut onions and garlic in butter until they are soft and translucent. Layer potato slices and onions in a 9 x 9 baking dish. Pour cream over the potatoes. Season to taste and sprinkle gruyere over the whole shebang. Bake 4050 minutes or until golden.

Preheat oven to 200. Place tomatoes and peppers, cut side down on a baking rack set onto a baking sheet. Roast for 20-30 minutes or until skins are easily removed. Spray or brush vegetables with olive oil and continue to roast until tomatoes become a dark red color, about 2 hours. Remove from oven and chop into small pieces. Meanwhile, cook and drain pasta. Place into a mixing bowl. Add the onions, tomatoes and peppers, toss to combine. Mix together the vinegar, mustard, parsley, basil, olive oil, salt and pepper. Beat with a whisk to combine. Pour over the pasta, add the cheese and toss again. Serve at room temperature.

Cover and cook potatoes in boiling salted water for 15 to 20 minutes, until potatoes are fork tender. Drain potatoes. Mash potatoes in a large mixing bowl until no lumps remain. Add butter and milk, salt, and pepper mashing in to blend together. Fold in pesto very lightly just to streak the potatoes. Garnish with pine nut and basil.

In a saucepan, melt butter. Stir in flour until smooth cook and stir over med heat for 2 minutes. Add cream, lemon juice, lemon zest and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for at least 5 minutes but do not boil. Garnish with chopped parsley and very thin slices of brussels sprouts.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees fahrenheit. Beat cream cheese at medium speed of electric mixer until fluffy. Mix in sugar. Add eggs one at a time, making sure the mixture is well blended. Stir in vanilla. Line 12 muffin cups with muffin paper, and place a chocolate wafer in each lined cup. Spoon the cream cheese mixture over the wafers. Bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees. Remove muffin tin from oven, but leave the cakes in the muffin pan and refrigerate them overnight. Remove the cheesecakes from the muffin pan. To serve, spoon a tablespoon of cherry pie filling on each mini cheesecake.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Lightly grease a 9 x 5 inch loaf pan. In a large mixing bowl, combine all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, baking powder, salt and brown sugar. Pour in beer, stir until a stiff batter is formed. It may be necessary to mix dough with your hands. Scrape dough into prepared loaf pan. Bake in preheated oven for 50-60 minutes, until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Pour into prepared muffin pans and bake at 375 for 20 to 25 minutes.

Heat oil in a large skillet over high heat. Season steaks generously on both side with salt and pepper. Place steaks in skillet. Cook, turning once, until browned, 2-3 minutes per side for medium rare. Transfer to a warmed plate, cover with foil. Add vinegar to skillet. Add garlic to skillet. Add tomato sauce to skillet. Cook,

Place salmon in 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over salmon. Turn salmon so that it gets coated with the marinade. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Bake in preheated 425 f oven for 10-12 minutes, or until fish flakes easily and is opaque in centre.

Place chicken breast halves in a resealable plastic bag set in a shallow dish. For marinade, stir together lime peel, lime juice, cooking oil, dried thyme, black pepper, salt, garlic cloves, salsa, lime wedgepreparation:Place chicken breast halves in a resealable plastic bag set in a shallow dish. For marinade, stir together lime peel, lime juice, cooking oil, dried thyme, black pepper, salt, garlic cloves, salsa, lime wedge

Preheat oven to 400f, grease a 15 x 10 inch baking pan. Mix together butter, oats, sugar, corn syrup, vanilla extract, salt, semisweet chocolate, walnutspreparation:Heat butter, sugar and water in a 3 quart sauce-pan to a rolling boil. When mix reaches 305 degrees pour onto a greased large cookie sheet. Sprinkle chocolate chips over the chocolate. As chocolate melts spread with a butter knife. Spread nuts evenly over the pan, shaking lightly until all nuts stick. Cool until hard. Break into pieces. Enjoy.

Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Place pasta in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in parsley. Serve over pasta topped with parmesan cheese.

Place the potatoes in a large skillet over medium heat, and cook for about 10 minutes, or until tender. Drain, and set aside to cool. In a large bowl, mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar, half of the onions, and half of the cheese. Gently stir in the cooled potatoes. Top with remaining cheese and onions, and sprinkle bacon bits over the top.

Preheat oven to 350f. Toss together apples and apples, spread evenly over bottom of 8x8 baking dish. In medium bowl combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and oats. Using pastry cutter work butter into oat mixture until crumbly. Spread over fruit, pressing down lightly. Bake 40-45 minutes or until top is lightly browned. Cool before serving. Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

Preheat oven to 400f. Cut off the ends of the brussels sprouts and pull off any yellow outer leaves. Mix them in a bowl with the olive oil, salt, and lemon-pepper seasoning. Transfer them to a sheet pan and roast for 35 to 40 minutes, until crisp outside and tender inside. Shake the pan from time to time to brown the brussels sprouts evenly. Sprinkle with more kosher salt, if you like, and serve hot.

Heat oven to 400f. Place squash, seeds still in, cut side up on a cookie sheet and bake for 45 minutes or until soft. Remove from oven and scoop out the seeds and fibers. Mix remaining ingredients and distribute evenly into the cavity of each squash. Return to oven for apprx 10 minutes.

Preheat oven to 400degf. Combine all ingredients on a large greased baking sheet. Arrange in a single layer. Roast in preheated oven for about 50 minutes, turning once during cooking, until potatoes are tender. Bake in the preheated oven until potatoes are tender, or about 45 minutes. Garnish with fresh rosemary sprigs.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. Cut off the ends of the brussels sprouts and pull off any yellow outer leaves. Mix them in a bowl with the olive oil, salt, and lemon-pepper seasoning. Transfer them to a sheet pan and roast for 35 to 40 minutes, until crisp outside and tender inside. Shake the pan from time to time to brown the brussels sprouts evenly. Sprinkle with more kosher salt, if you like, and serve hot.

Preheat oven to 375f. Place chicken pieces in 13x9-inch baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. Arrange onion slices over top. In small saucepan, combine ketchup, brown sugar, worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and liquid smoke. Heat over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes or until sugar dissolves. Pour over chicken. Bake for 30 minutes. In small saucepan combine the tomato sauce, sugar and soy sauce and cook until the sugar has dissolved. After the chicken wings are cooked, thickly spread the sauce over the wings and bake for 30 to 40 minutes or longer or until browned and very tender. Serve warm.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees f. In a large bowl, cream brown sugar and melted butter. Add vanilla and eggs 1 at a time. In a separate bowl, sift flour, powder, and salt. Add dry mixture into wet mixture. Spread into a greased glass baking dish. Cook in oven until golden, 15-18 minutes. In a microwave safe bowl, heat peanut butter and cream on low heat. Stir until smooth, and spread over baked bars. Cool slightly and cut into bars.
Heat oven to 350 degrees. Mix butter, sugar, baking powder, salt, vanilla extract, milk, egg, salt, walnuts, cinnamon, peaches and bake for 15 minutes.

Preheat grill on high for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, over medium heat, combine brown sugar, apple juice, canola oil, soy sauce, ginger, salt and pepper to taste, bring to a boil. In a measuring cup or small bowl, whisk cornstarch into the water and mix into brown sugar mixture. Cook, stirring constantly until bubbling and thickened. Reduce grill to medium-high heat. Grill chops on oiled grill, brushing often with brown sugar glaze, about 6-8 minutes per side, or until digital thermometer inserted sideways into the center of each chop reads 160f do not over cook.

Add liquid and spices to crockpot. Slice meat into thin strips. Toss meat in crockpot mixture. Cook on low for 6-8 hours. One hour before serving add broccoli. Cover and simmer for 10-12 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add in the sausage and spinach. Cook until well heated.

In blender, combine eggs, milk, white sugar, milk, salt. Blend 10 seconds. Stir in coconut. Pour into greased pie plate. Bake in 350 oven 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted in the middle. Serve hot or chilled.
Cover crock pot with aluminum foil, leaving enough to overlap potatoes when finished. Layer half of potatoes, onions, potatoes and cheese in crock pot. Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 9 hours.

Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Cut chicken in half. Arrange, skin side up, in a roasting pan. Combine butter, lemon juice, and spices in a small bowl and mix well. Brush chicken with mixture. Roast until juices run clear. Broil 6 inches from heat for 3 minutes.

In a large skillet, saute king prawns jumbo shrimp cherry tomatoes and lemon in vegetable oil until tender. Add butter, garlic cloves, cherry tomatoes, king prawns, lemon zest, fresh ground black pepper, flat leaf parsley, lemon zest, fresh ground black pepper, flat leaf parsley, lemon zest, fresh ground black pepper, flat leaf parsley, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon zest, lemon

Spray a nonstick frypan with veggies cooking spray and heat to medium. Spray veggie cooking spray over both sides of the cod fillets. Squeese 2 lemon sections over cod surfaces. Sprinkle parsley, italian seasoning, salt and pepper over both sides of the cod filets. Place cod into medium hot frypan, cook for about 5 minutes, carefully turn and cook a further 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Serve hot with the other 2 lemon sections for garnish.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Lightly grease cookie sheet. Beat sugar and shortening until creamy. Beat in egg, milk and orange extract. Stir in flour and baking powder. Add cereal and nuts. Mix well. Drop by tablespoon onto prepared cookie sheet. Bake 10-12 minutes or until lightly browned. Let stand 1 minute before removing to racks to cool.

Place pork chops in greased slow cooker. Top with onions and mushrooms. Combine soup mix, water, and mushroom soup. Pour over mushrooms and onions. Cover. Cook on low 6-8 hours or high 4-5. Serve over rice or cooked noodles.

In a large skillet, melt butter over medium-low heat. Add carrots, onions, and ginger, cover and cook, stirring, for about 7 to 10 minutes, until just tender. Stir in the orange juice, jelly, and salt. Cook, uncovered, for about 4 minutes, stirring frequently, until vegetables are tender and nicely glazed with the jelly and orange juice mixture. Sprinkle with fresh chopped parsley just before serving.
Place chicken in crock pot and cover with lid. Cover and cook on low for 8-10 hours. Serve gravy over meat and vegetables.

Preheat oven to 350f. In a large mixing bowl, cream your butter and sugars til fluffy and airy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in flour mixture until combined well drop by quarter cup measure on to an ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12 to 13 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from baking sheet and then cool on wire rack.

Spray rack of boiler pan with nonstick spray. Preheat the broiler. Whisk together the brown sugar, mustard, and dill in a small bowl. Sprinkle on the broiler rack and spoon the brown sugar glaze on top. Position 7 inches from the heat and broil until lightly browned and just opaque in the center, about 6 minutes.

Place chicken legs in slow cooker. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours, until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a fork. Serve garnished with chopped peanuts and additional fresh cilantro.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour a bundt pan. I use bakers joy spray. Beat cake mix, water, oil, eggs and pineapple on low speed 3 minutes. Stir in nuts and raisins. Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 50-55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack. Cool at least 1 hour before frosting.

Preheat oven to 325 degrees f. In a large, heavy skillet over medium-high heat, brown ground beef, and drain fat. Mix in dry taco seasoning. Spoon browned meat into a 9x13 inch glass baking dish. Spoon a layer of refried beans over meat, then salsa. Top with shredded cheese. Bake about 20 to 25 minutes in the preheated oven.

Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add zucchini, shallots, fresh parsley, extra virgin olive oil, salt and pepper. Cook, tossing and stirring occasionally for 3 minutes. Add mushrooms, sundried-tomatoes, broth and basil, if using. Cook, tossing and stirring constantly, until zucchini are crisp-tender and the basil are sofened and have just begun to release their liquid, about 2 minutes. Remove skillet from the heat and season with salt and pepper. Serve immediately.

Preheat oven to 450 degrees f. Heat 2 large roasting pans in the oven for 5 minutes. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, toss the zucchini with the olive oil and crushed red pepper. Season generously with salt and pepper. Spread the zucchini on the hot pans and roast for 30 minutes without stirring, until the rounds are tender and their bottom are golden. Transfer to a platter, garnish with mint and serve.
Place all the ingredients in a bowl. Beat until combined well. Pour into a greased 9 inch pie pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes.

Heat oven to 400 degrees f. Cover broiler pan or cookie sheet with foil and spread asparagus in one layer. Spray with cooking spray and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cook for 12 minutes or less. Heat butter in a small skillet on low heat until lightly brown. Add vinegar and soy sauce. Pour over cooked asparagus.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees fahrenheit or 175 degrees celsius. Mix the flour, baking powder, and baking soda together in a bowl. Set the mixture aside. Cream the butter and sugar. Beat in the egg and vanilla extract. Once combined, slowly blend in the dry ingredients until evenly mixed. Searate dough into tablespoon-sized balls. Place onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Place on center rack and bake for 5 to 7 minutes. Let the cookies sit for 2 minutes before cooling on wire racks.

In a large saucepan bring water to a boil. Add chicken broth and water to a boil. Add onion, carrot and garlic. Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 10 minutes. In a skillet cook and stir chicken in hot oil for 3 minutes or until larger pieces of pasta are tender but slightly firm. Add chicken

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Lightly grease an 8x8-inch baking dish. In a large mixing bowl, beat together milk, butter and egg substitute. Add the sugar, then gradually beat in the flour. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes. Cut into 16 square servings.

Place chicken in crockpot. Sprinkle with soup mix and garlic salt. Pour dressing and water over chicken. Cover and cook on low for 8-9 hours. Remove chicken and cool slightly. Skim fat from cooking juices. Remove chicken from bones and cut into bite-size pieces and return to crockpot. Serve with a slotted spoon on buns. I have also used boneless chicken pieces and cut them up before placing in the crockpot. You just need to adjust cooking time if doing it this way.

Place broccoli florets, bacon, dried cranberries, sunflower seeds, mayonnaise, sugar, white wine vinegar, shredded cheddar cheese in a large mixing bowl. Pour dressing over salad mixture, stirring well. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours to allow flavors to blend. Cover and
Cover with lid and switch to high. Add prepared salmon. Cover and cook for 4 hours. Serve in warmed deep soup plates.

Preheat oven to 325f. Lightly grease 9 x 5 loaf pan. In a large bowl, combine the flour, baking soda and salt. In a separate bowl, cream together butter and brown sugar. Stir in eggs and mashed bananas until well blended. Stir banana mixture into flour mixture. Stir just to moisten. Pour batter into prepared loaf pan. Bake in preheated oven for 60-65 minutes until a toothpick inserted into center of loaf comes out clean. Let bread cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack to cool.

Heat large non-stick skillet, swirl in oil, then add grapes. Saute 30 seconds. Add walnuts in two batches, cook til just browned, about 2 minutes. Drain pasta, add to bowl with yogurt dressing. Add steak and tomatoes, toss to coat. Serve immediately.

In a large saucepan, stir together the cocoa and sugar. Add water. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Allow to boil for two minutes, still stirring. Add milk and orange peel and heat to serving temperature. Add vanilla and serve.

Heat oven to 350 degrees fahrenheit. In large skillet, brown beef and onion then drain. Return meat to pan. Add spaghetti sauce. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl combine mozzarella cheese and sour cream. Pour hot meat into an ungreased 12 x 8 inch dish. Spoon cheese mixture over meat. Unroll crescent roll dough over the top of the mixture. Mix parmesan cheese and butter together, then spread over the top of the dough. Bake 18-25 minutes or until golden brown.

Combine yogurt, curry powder, coriander, chicken breasts, basmati rice, vegetable stock cubes, carrot, red pepper, green chilies, mint, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies, green chilies

Preheat oven to 350 degrees fahrenheit or 175 degrees celsius. Mix the flour, baking powder, baking soda, butter, sugar, egg, vanilla extract, cornmeal, baking powder, salt, flour. Add to the creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven about 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. Line 9 inch pie pan with pastry. In large bowl combine all filling ingredients except butter and toss lightly. Spoon filling into crust lined pan. Cut 4 slits in top of crust. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Cover edge of crust with strips of foil after 20 minutes of baking to prevent excessive browning. Cover edge of crust with strips of foil after 20 minutes

In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and soup until no longer lumpy. Pour over chicken in the bottom of a skillet. Cover and cook chicken until done and no longer pink. In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and soup until no longer lumpy. Bake in a 350 degree oven for 1 hour, checking after 45 minutes to make sure they do not get over-cooked.

Place turkey breast in crock pot and cover with lid. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours or on low for 8 to 10 hours. Remove meat and vegetables and some of the cooking liquid. Slice meat thinly across the grain. Serve with vegetables and some of the liquid.

Place chicken breast halves in a resealable plastic bag set in a shallow dish. For marinade, stir together lime peel, lime juice, oil, thyme, pepper, salt, lime slice, red bell pepper, cilantropreparation:Place chicken breast halves in a resealable plastic bag set in a shallow dish. For marinade, stir together lime peel, lime juice, oil, thyme, pepper, salt, lime slice, red bell pepper, cilantropreparation:

Mix all the ingredients together in a glass bowl. Cover tightly with plastic wrap. Place lamb in a extra large heavy-duty plastic bag or glass bowl. Pour the marinade over the lamb, and turn to coat well on all sides. Place in the fridge for a minimum of 24 hours. When ready to grill, remove from fridge and save marinade for basting if desired. Turn the grill to high heat. Sear both sides for about 5 minutes on each side. Reduce grill temperature to medium heat and finish cooking the lamb. You may baste the lamb with the leftover marinade if desired.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees place scrubbed whole sweet potatoes in a baking dish and cook until tender. In a saucepan, heat oil and pepper over medium high heat until browned on all sides. Discard pepper, add garlic and ginger and cook until barely tender. Stir in salt and balsamic vinegar to taste and simmer over low heat until ready to serve. When tender, split each potato, drizzle with ginger sauce and serve hot.

Heat oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken, and sprinkle with pepper flakes. Stir fry 3 minutes. Add vegetables and teriyaki sauce. Stir fry 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender and chicken is thoroughly cooked.

Put the croissants in a greased 13x9 inch baking dish. In a mixing bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, ground nutmeg, cinnamon raisin bread, unsalted butter, maple syrup. Pour egg mixture evenly over the croissants. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight. Remove from refrigerator 20 minutes before baking. Preheat oven to 350. Bake, uncovered, for 45-50 minutes or until golden brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve with maple syrup, if desired.

Combine ingredients in a large bowl. Toss cabbage, red bell pepper, fresh cilantro, jalapeno, olive oil, fresh lime juice, ground cumin. Toss dressing with the cabbage, red bell pepper, fresh cilantro, jalapeno, olive oil, fresh lime juice, ground cumin. Toss dressing with the cabbage, red bell pepper, fresh cilantro, jal

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a small micorwave safe bowl combine sugar, cold water, semisweet chocolate, unsweetened chocolate, lightly-salted butter, whipping cream, scotch whisky, poundcake, fresh strawberries, fresh pineapple. Place cubed potatoes in a large bowl and pour honey mixture over potatoes, toss to coat. Place in a roasting pan, salt and bake for about 50 minutes, or until tender, stirring occasionally.

Preheat the oven to 400 degrees f. Whisk together the olive oil, balsamic vinegar, thyme, garlic, salt, pepper and brown sugar. Cut the tomatoes in half and toss to combine with the olive oil mixture. Spread the tomatoes in a roasting pan and place in the oven. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes or until the tomatoes are shrivelled. Break the ends from the asparagus at their natural breaking point. Add the tender lengths of asparagus to the tomatoes and continue to cook for 25 minutes or until the asparagus is tender.

Preheat oven to 400. Stir flour, baking soda and salt together. Cut in butter. Beat egg and milk slightly in separate bowl. Milk together. Kneed on floured surface. Roll till desired thickness. Cut out with a glass or cookie cutter. Bake for 15 - 20 minutes at 175c.

In a large pot of boiling, salted water cook the pasta to al dente and drain. Return to the pot and melt in the butter. Toss to coat. Whisk together the eggs, milk, hot sauce, salt, pepper, and mustard. Stir into the pasta and add the cheese. Over low heat continue to stir for 3 minutes or until creamy.

In large skillet, heat italian dressing and cook fish over medium heat, turning once, 8 minutes or until fish flakes. Remove to serving platter and keep warm. Into skillet, add wine, then pepper, dill and mustard. Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring occasionally, 8 minutes. Stir in cream and heat 1 minute or until thickened. Serve over fish. Garnish, if desired, with baby vegetables.

Preheat oven to 350 degree f. In a large pot heat butter and saut onions. Add milk, flour, salt and pepper. Bring to a rolling boil. Slowly add cheddar cheese, stirring while adding. Drain macaroni. Add macaroni directly to the cheese mixture in the pot. Pour mac and cheese mixture into large lasagna pan. Put in oven and bake for 30 minutes or until top is bubbly and golden brown.

Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Spray muffin cups with non-stick vegetable spray. Roll out biscuits until each is big enough to fit into muffin tins with enough dough to cover. Mix together catsup and mustard with ground beef. Fill each biscuit cup with meat mixture. Sprinkle cheese over all. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

In a small saucepan, heat butter and oil over medium heat. Saute onion until softened, about 5 minutes. Add couscous, cumin and cayenne, stirring constantly, for 1 minute. Adjust heat to medium-high, add couscous, blend well and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add chicken broth, stir to incorporate, and bring to boiling point. Cover pan, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork, season with salt if needed, and serve hot.

Heat oil on medium high heat in large skillet or frying pan. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper in a bag. Shake chicken pieces, one at a time, in bag to coat with flour mixture. Place chicken skin side down in baking pan. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes. Turn chicken. Bake 30 minutes longer.

Preheat oven to 210c place the mixed herbs, breadcrumbs, salt and pepper in a large bowl and mix until combined, then set aside. Place the flour in another bowl and the eggs in a third bowl. Toss the chicken pieces into the egg, then the breadcrumbs, pressing to coat well. Once all the chicken is crumbed, heat a little oil in a large non-stick frying pan. Cook the chicken in batches until golden. Remove and transfer to a baking tray lined with baking paper. Place in oven for 4-5 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. Serve chicken with lemon wedges and a little whole egg mayonnaise for dipping, if desired.

In a large skillet, cook the beef, seasoned salt, garlic powder, carrots and onions until beef is browned and veggies are crisp tender. Drain and return to skillet. Add water, cabbage, green peppers, soy sauce and seasoning packet from the noodles. Break noodles into small pieces, add to pan and stir well to cover noodles with liquid. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and noodles are tender.

Slice avocado lengthwise. Remove pit and scoop avocado into a small bowl. Add mayonnaise, lime juice, worcestershire sauce, hot pepper sauce, garlic salt and salt. Stir and mash the ingredients together until guacamole is preferred consistency. Serve immediately, or cover and refrigerate if desired.
Heat oven to 400f. Add 1 tb olive oil in a large bowl. Add lamb. Turn to coat. Let marinate at room temperature at least 30 minutes and up to 1 hour. Preheat oven to 400f. Preheat oven

Preheat oven to 200c. Lightly grease a 26 x 16cm baking pan. Line with baking paper. Place apple sauce, fruit, sugar and all seeds in a bowl, mix to combine. Add oats, flour, coconut and eggs. Mix to combine. Place mixture in baking pan, use a flat bladed knife or spatula to spead evenly. Bake for 25 minutes, or until cooked and golden. Turn onto wire rack to cool. Cut into 8 piecec. Wrap in baking paper, then plastic wrap to store.

Muddle basil leaves, 1 lime wedge and simple syrup. Add ice, rum and orange juice. Shake vigorously for 20 seconds or until ice crystals form. With a cocktail strainer, pour into a tall ice-filled glass. Top off with club soda. Garnish edge of glass with a slice of lime.

Heat oven to 400 f. Combine the oil, garlic, sugar, cumin, salt, cinnamon, and carrots in a shallow baking pan. Roast 20 minutes or until fork-tender. Remove from oven and add the raisins, lemon juice, and parsley. Toss well.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Mix spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and water. Spoon 1 cup onto bottom of 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Layer half the ravioli and 1 cup shredded cheese over sauce mixture. Top with remaining ravioli and sauce mixture. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Cover. Bake 30 minutes. Uncover. Bake 15 minutes or until ravioli is tender and heated through. Let stand 10 minutes.

Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the quinoa. Mix well. Cook until the quinoa is cooked through, stirring constantly. Pour over the spinach mixture, tossing to coat. Season with the salt and pepper. Sprinkle with the parmesan cheese.

Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add in onion and saute until golden. Add in sliced cabbage, cider vinegar, sugar, celery seeds and black pepper. Mix to combine and cook until the cabbage if crisp-tender and the liquid is reduced to a glaze. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat oven to 350 degrees. Mix the flour, baking powder, baking soda, baking powder, salt, baking soda, pecans. Mix, do not beat. Stir in pecans. Baked in greased loaf pan in a 350 preheated oven about 1 hour. Best kept a day or two before eating. Freezes well, great thinly sliced with cream cheese.

Mix together the basting sauce ingredients and stir until smooth. Cover and let sit in refrigerator at least 1 hour. Prepare your grill medium to medium-high heat. Place ham slices on prepared grill and baste with some of the sauce. Grill for 1 hour, basting and turning every 15 minutes.

In a small bowl whisk together first five ingredients and set aside. Crush sesame seed with a motar and pestle, then spread evenly in a pie plate. Coat the tuna steaks with the crushed seeds.
